    "However, to significantly scale up this respect of FL not only requires new techniques, but also new experiment designs for improved evaluation.",
    "Although recent studies have started to evaluate new FL methods with larger base models, they are still markedly smaller than FMs which are achieving breakthrough performance under centralized training settings.We list the methods reviewed alongside with the largest base models involved in their evaluations in Table III and Table IV.",
    "The substantial difference for model sizes between existing FL research and centralized FMs might cast doubts on the feasibility and practicality of the FL techniques for FedFM, calling for further experimental studies involving large-scale FMs.",
